HEADWORD: Tout-ensemble
<hw>Tout`-en`sem"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <def>All together; hence, in costume, the fine arts,
etc., the general effect of a work as a whole, without regard to the
execution of the separate perts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Touter</ent>⟦br⟧
